<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIENDSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As I was drinking my morning coffee, I read Al Martinez's column about the 
friendship of a blind woman and a gay man that began in their high school days 
and ended with his tragic death in an auto accident ("Time and the Deep 
Winters," Metro, Nov. 28). The beautifully written article brought tears to my 
eyes and reminded me of the verse a friend recently enclosed in a little 
thank-you note: "If we had all the earth's riches we could never spend enough 
to buy the treasures the heart finds in a friend." 
</P>
<P>
Thank you, Mr. Martinez, for reminding me what this time of year should really 
be about: extending the hand of human kindness instead of those needless, mad 
dashes to shopping malls for unappreciated Christmas gifts. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT LITMAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
