<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHILIPPINE COUP ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As one of the many Filipino immigrants living here in Los Angeles, I am deeply 
saddened by the recent military attempt in the Philippines. 
</P>
<P>
However, I feel that the Filipino people and the world should not totally 
discredit Aquino. People must understand that the country's economy was at its 
lowest possible point when Aquino took over. The economy has improved by 4% 
since she became president. It took 20 long years for the Filipino people to 
react to all of Marcos' political wrongdoings and corruption. The least they 
can do now to contribute to the country's stability is to give Aquino a break 
and a little more time. 
</P>
<P>
A coup attempt like this only puts the economy further down and discourages 
foreign investors from doing business in the Philippines. What Filipinos should 
work on is the establishment of discipline and unity as a people. There can be 
no growth and progress without these vital factors. 
</P>
<P>
SOCKIE CARRIEDO 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
