<P>
POLICE, BLACK LEADERS MEET OVER SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police officials in Ft. Lauderdale, Fla., met with black leaders to discuss the 
apparent accidental shooting of an unarmed black man by a white policeman 
during a drug search. Black leaders later told reporters they were satisfied 
with the way the case was being handled. Patrick Lavon Lee, 28, was shot in the 
back of the head in a predominantly black neighborhood by police officer Robert 
Thomas McCabe. Lee was in critical condition at Broward General Medical Center 
and was not expected to recover, doctors said. The shooting was the second 
involving a police officer and an unarmed suspect in South Florida since a 
Miami jury last week convicted police officer William Lozano of manslaughter in 
the deaths of two black men. 
</P>
</TEXT>
