<P>
INTOXICATION DENIED IN CRASH FATAL TO 27 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man charged with 27 counts of murder as a result of a bus crash last year had 
not been drinking heavily the day of the accident, relatives and a friend 
testified as the defense opened its case in Carrollton, Ky. The defendant, 
Larry Mahoney, 36, of Worthville, admits drinking the day of the crash, driving 
on the wrong side of Interstate 71 and striking the loaded church bus. But the 
defense maintains that the 27 victims were killed because the bus was unsafe. 
The fuel tank of the bus owned by the Radcliff First Assembly of God church 
exploded, sending flames throughout the bus carrying 67 people home from an 
outing. 
</P>
