<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BLACK PICKED FOR CITY POST IN WAKE OF BIAS 
PROTESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After months of protests by the NAACP that blacks are not represented in top 
administrative posts in Carson city government, City Administrator Jack Smith 
has chosen a black woman, Lorraine A. Oten, as finance director. 
</P>
<P>
Smith said Oten, whose salary range in her new job is $60,000 to $77,000, "was 
selected solely on her experience and skills." But he added that he is pleased 
that Oten, who is leaving a position as finance director of Lynwood, will add 
balance to Carson's administrative team. 
</P>
<P>
"It does something to appease a segment of our community who were crying out 
for more representation," he said. 
</P>
<P>
In Carson city government, four white men and an Asian man are the other 
appointed department heads. Smith is white and the deputy city administrator is 
an Asian man. The elected city clerk is an Asian woman, and the elected city 
treasurer is a white woman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
