<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PRIESTESS GETS 360 DAYS FOR PROBATION 
VIOLATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A convicted prostitute who says she has had intercourse with 2,000 men as the 
high priestess of an ancient sex-worshiping church was sentenced in Los Angeles 
Monday to 360 days in jail for a probation violation. 
</P>
<P>
Mary Ellen Tracy, 46, the self-proclaimed high priestess, was found by 
Municipal Judge Marion Obera to have violated her probation because of her 
arrest Nov. 14 on suspicion of pandering. Tracy immediately posted bail to 
avoid going to jail while the city attorney's office determines whether it will 
file a misdemeanor charge against her stemming from the Nov. 14 arrest. 
</P>
<P>
Obera on Sept. 22 placed Tracy on three years' probation and sentenced her to 
90 days in County Jail after she was convicted of operating a house of 
prostitution. Tracy posted bail to delay serving that sentence while appealing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
