Woodard, yet managed to forge a second-half rally to defeat Venice, 54-44, in a 
nonleague game Tuesday at Taft. 
</P>
<P>
The Toreadors trailed, 21-17, in the first half, but outscored Venice, 37-23, 
in the second half. Jason Deyoe led the way with 12 points and a game-high 13 
rebounds. 
