<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH VOWS ACTION ON DRUNK DRIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush, calling drunk driving "one of the most deadly scourges" of our 
times, promised Monday to keep up pressure to get intoxicated drivers off the 
road. 
</P>
<P>
Bush signed legislation declaring this National Drunk and Drugged Driving 
Awareness Week and issued a proclamation saying: "As we prepare to celebrate 
the holidays and rejoice in the promise of the new year, it is fitting that we 
pause to remember the perils of drinking and driving." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
DRUNK DRIVING; BUSH, GEORGE; LEGISLATION -- UNITED STATES; PRESIDENTIAL 
PROCLAMATIONS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121289-0098 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 147431 </DOCID>
<DATE>
