<P>
NEW TREASURER SWORN IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Catalina Vasquez Villalpando took the oath of office Monday as U.S. Treasurer, 
the official whose signature goes on every bill. Treasury Secretary Nicholas F. 
Brady administered the oath to Villalpando, a former senior executive of 
Communications International Inc. 
