<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE CHARS SIMI FREEWAY AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A brush fire charred about 15 acres near the Simi Valley Freeway in Chatsworth 
early today before it was controlled, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was reported at 4:13 a.m. just north of the freeway near De Soto 
Avenue, said Fire Department spokesman Jim Wells. 
</P>
<P>
It took 35 firefighters, assisted by three water-dropping helicopters, about 30 
minutes to put out the blaze, Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries and no structures were threatened, he said. The cause of 
the fire is under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
