</P>
<P>
NO DATE YET FOR TV NHL REPLAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTREAL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No date has been set for the National Hockey League to begin using television 
replays to decide disputed goals but the system will probably be adopted, a 
league spokesman said today. 
</P>
<P>
"There is no resolution yet," NHL spokesman Gary Meagher said in response to a 
report in the Toronto Star that the league would begin using replays for the 
Stanley Cup playoffs in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
The league will experiment with replays during the preseason in 1990, the 
newspaper reported. Only the referee would be allowed to seek a television 
ruling, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Meagher said replays were discussed at an NHL general managers meeting in 
Chicago last month and will be on the agenda at the next meeting in January at 
Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
