<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MCCALLUM TO DEFEND WBA TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DUBLIN, Ireland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jamaican Mike McCallum will defend his World Boxing Assn. middleweight title 
against Ireland's Steve Collins on Feb. 3, promoters said today. 
</P>
<P>
Collins, the WBA's fifth-ranked middleweight, will fight the champion at the 
4,000-seat Point Depot, a new arena along the waterfront in Dublin. 
</P>
<P>
McCallum was scheduled to defend his crown against Briton Michael Watson last 
month in London, but the top-ranked challenger broke his nose during training 
and had to pull out of the fight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
