<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO $145,000 WINNERS IN OHIO TRIFECTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NORTH RANDALL, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two bettors correctly picked the top three finishers in the fifth and seventh 
races at Thistledown on Monday, winning $145,421.60 each in a track record Twin 
Trifecta payout. 
</P>
<P>
The winning combinations were 9-8-11 in the fifth race and 3-1-8 in the seventh 
race on the closing day of the 50-day Cranwood meeting. 
</P>
<P>
The crowd of 6,682 bet $1,294,983, a closing day record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
